In order to test this code you will need to got to the PIO menu.
In the advanced tab you will see test.
Press test.
Press the boot button on the ESP32.
wait.
The terminal will demand a reboot of the board.
reboot the board (press EN btn)
 

 ALL THE FOLDERS THAT CONTAIN TESTS NEED TO START with 'test_'
    the .cpp files in those folders will be called.

In order not to make the testing process a lengthy endeavor there
is a single file called (test/test_c/test.cpp).

Write your tests in the test_c directory and include the .h file in test.cpp.
